description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/ble_ipsp_transport.c
Lines: 513-530

In lichen_ble_slip_send(), if bt_gatt_notify_cb() fails partway through sending a fragmented packet:

    while (offset < slip_len) {
        ...
        err = bt_gatt_notify_cb(transport_state.conn, &params);
        if (err) {
            LOG_WRN("Notify failed (err %d), sent %zu/%zu", err, offset, slip_len);
            transport_state.stats.tx_errors++;
            break;  // Exit loop, partial send
        }
        offset += send_len;
    }

The function breaks out of the loop and returns the error, but:
1. A partial SLIP frame has been sent to the client
2. The client will receive an incomplete frame
3. No indication to the caller that data was partially sent
4. No mechanism to resume or rollback

While this isn't a memory leak per se, it's a protocol-level data corruption - the remote end receives a truncated SLIP frame which it may try to process.

Fix: Consider buffering the entire frame server-side before sending any chunks, or add a return value that indicates partial send (bytes actually sent vs requested).
